The '''Chepangic languages''', [[Chepang language|Chepang]] and [[Bhujel language|Bhujel]], are [[Sino-Tibetan languages]] of uncertain affiliation spoken in Nepal. They are often classified as part of the [[Mahakiranti languages|Mahakiranti]] or [[Magaric languages|Magaric]] families (van Driem 2001).
Until recently, the [[Chepang people]] were [[hunter-gatherer]]s.
