{{Infobox language | name = Mah Meri | altname = Besisi, Betise’ | states = [[Malaysia]] | region = [[Peninsular Malaysia|Malay Peninsula]] | speakers = 2,990 | date = 2003 | ref = e18 | familycolor = Austroasiatic | fam2 = [[Aslian languages|Aslian]] | fam3 = [[Southern Aslian languages|Southern Aslian]] | iso3 = mhe | glotto = besi1244 | glottorefname = Besisi }}
'''Mah Meri''', sometimes also known as '''Besisi''' or '''Betise’''', is an [[Austroasiatic languages|Austroasiatic language]] spoken in the Malay Peninsula. It belongs to the [[Southern Aslian languages|Southern]] Aslian branch of the [[Aslian languages|Aslian]] languages. It is the only remaining Aslian language spoken in a coastal area. A dictionary of the Mah Meri language has been compiled by Nicole Kruspe.
