{{redirect|Gbi language|the Kru language|Gbii language}} {{Infobox language |name=West Banda |altname=Golo |states=[[Central African Republic]], [[South Sudan]] |speakers=7,500 |date=1982–1996 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam1=[[Ubangian languages|Ubangian]] |fam2=[[Banda languages|Banda]] |fam3= |iso3=bbp |glotto=west2458 |glottorefname=West Central Banda }}
'''West Banda''' is a minor [[Banda languages|Banda language]], spoken by 10,000 or so people.{{citation needed|date=October 2011}}. Dialects: Dakpa, Gbaga-Nord (Gbaga-2), Gbi, Vita, Wojo (Hodjo).
